  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Legal definitions typically include:\n\n1. Concealing the source of illegally obtained funds\n2. Transforming criminal proceeds into seemingly legitimate assets\n3. Deliberately disguising the origins of money from criminal activities\n\nSpecific legal elements often include:\n- Intentional financial transactions\n- Knowing the funds originate from criminal activity\n- Attempting to make illegal funds appear legal\n- Transferring or converting criminal proceeds\n\nSpecific definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most include similar core components related to disguising illegal financial sources.\n\nWould you like me to discuss specific legal frameworks or provide more technical details about money laundering definitions?",
